''See also [[mémorable]]''
==English==

===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''[[memorabilis]]'', from ''[[memorare]]'' to bring to remembrance, from ''[[memor]]'' mindful, remembering.  See [[memory]], and confer [[memorabilia]]. 

===Adjective===
'''memorable'''  ({{compar}}: '''more memorable''', {{superl}}: '''most memorable''')

# Worthy to be remembered; very important or remarkable.
#:''Surviving fame to gain, Buy tombs, by books, by '''memorable''' deeds.''  -Sir J. Davies.

